{
  "texts": [
    "An additional effect is that extant research in English may inform the development of assessment frameworks in other languages.",
    "For example, a twotier model has been proposed to assess intelligibility in non-English speakers with dysarthria.",
    "This model encodes speech acoustically and interprets it through the phonological or prosodic structures of the target language (Yeo et al, 2025).",
    "However, in the rush to publish new findings, researchers must prioritize transparency, documenting data collection, model training, validation steps, and theoretical interpretation of AI outputs.",
    "SLPs must remain the ultimate fact-checkers and upholders of truth in the discipline and papers published openly without peer review will need to be periodically updated."
  ]
}